==English==

===Etymology===
Japanese [[合掌]] ''gasshō'', from  [[合]] (''gatsu'') '[[unite]]' and [[掌]] (''shō'') '[[palm]]'.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A ritual [[gesture]] of Eastern origin, with [[hand]]s pressed together in front of the chest. It can be used for [[prayer]] or as a sign of [[greeting]], [[gratitude]], [[reverence]], or [[apology]]. When performed with a bow, it is called [[gassho rei]].

